<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573404>
    dc:description "Fig. 2.—Dorsal, ventral, and lateral views of skull and lateral view of mandible of an adult female Sciurus anomalus (University of Kansas Biodiversity Institute [KU] #105169) from Yatağan, Denizli Province, Turkey.Greatest length of skull is 51.4mm. Used with permission of the photographer Jeb Zirato." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573404/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573406>
    dc:description "Fig. 3.—Geographic distribution of Sciurus anomalus modified from Thorington et al. (2012) with subspecific ranges denoted as: 1, S. a. anomalus; 2, S. a. pallescens; 3, S. a. syriacus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573406/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573408>
